THE OSLO BREAKFAST
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    
    The people who kindly agreed to house children evacuated
    from Britain's cities during the second World War faced a number
    of unexpected difficulties. The first was vermin - body lice. Some
    children, particularly from inner city slums, were so verminous
    that their clothes - not that they had many of them - had to be
    burnt on arrival at their new evacuation homes in the country...

